---
title: History of Programming Languages
theme: our-timeline
---
timeline
    title History of Programming Languages

    section Foundations
        1954 : FORTRAN
             : First high-level compiled language
        1958 : LISP
             : Functional programming pioneer
        1960 : COBOL
             : Business data processing

    section Systems Era
        1969 : C
             : Systems programming revolution
        1972 : Smalltalk
             : Object-oriented concepts
        1983 : C++
             : OOP meets systems programming

    section Scripting Wave
        1987 : Perl
             : Text processing & web CGI
        1991 : Python
             : Readable & general-purpose
        1995 : Java
             : Write once, run anywhere
             : JVM ecosystem

    section Modern Languages
        2003 : Scala
             : Functional + OOP on JVM
        2009 : Go
             : Systems + concurrency
        2010 : Rust
             : Memory safety without GC
        2014 : Swift
             : Apple platform modernisation
